Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text: Lynden is a charming town just south of the Canadian border and northeast of Bellingham. It was settled by Dutch farmers, and continues to boast 50% Dutch heritage. The downtown was built to replicate the historic brick buildings of the Netherlands with street-lined colorful flowers. Lynden is a tourist destination with plenty of personality. In addition to tourist traffic, it has a strong local economy and community.
